<title>PORTUGAL: Green shoe exercised in Mota cap increase.</title>
<headline>Green shoe exercised in Mota cap increase.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-07-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>A &quot;green shoe&quot; for 400,000 shares in a capital increase by Portuguese construction company Mota &amp; Companhia was exercised at 2,950 escudos per share, a source in leader Banco Essi told Reuters.  </p>
<p>The source said that a total of 4.86 million Mota shares were sold in the capital increase.</p>
<p>-- Lisbon newsroom +(351-1) 3538254</p>
